   {:e #blake3 "9802ad357895e07f5d947b64dcb8251d9e1736e1ee63b0d0e65609bb2ca96645" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Task inflation is a structural problem, not just an administrative one. The system creates tasks faster than it closes them. Even after ADM-1/ADM-2 (batch close + EPIC triage), the root cause remains: no decay mechanism, no auto-close, no lifecycle management. RATIONALE: NEG-010 (do not open loops). The task system itself has become an open loop — it generates but doesn't converge. APPROACH: Two structural improvements: (1) Task decay — auto-downgrade untouched tasks to P4 after 5 sessions. (2) EPIC auto-close — when all sub-tasks of an EPIC are closed, auto-close the EPIC. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After 5 sessions, stale tasks auto-decay to P4. (B) EPICs with all closed sub-tasks auto-close. (C) R(t) impact concentration improves (top-1 impact greater than 0.35). SPEC: Need new INV-TASK-NNN for task lifecycle. Prerequisite spec creation included as sub-task." :op :assert}
